25
00:02:19,760 --> 00:02:23,920
structure catering to businessmen and their hookers who don't want to be entertained.

26
00:02:24,480 --> 00:02:28,720
Edie and her colleagues didn't think he was active, but just beyond the safe side,

27
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:32,960
we had one of our own telepaths, Mr. G.G. Ashwood, go in and read him.

28
00:02:33,920 --> 00:02:37,440
Ashwood found a scramble pattern surrounding Malapone's mind,

29
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:42,960
so he couldn't do anything. He therefore went back to Topeka, Kansas,

30
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:49,280
where he's currently scouting a new possibility. Runciter, more awake now, had lit a cigarette.

31
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:54,480
Chin in hand, he sat propped up somberly, smoke drifting across the scanner of his

32
00:02:54,480 --> 00:03:00,880
end of the bi-channel circuit. You're sure the teap was Malapone? Nobody seems to know what he looks

33
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:06,000
like. He must use a different physiognomic template every month. What about his field?

34
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:10,400
We asked Joe Chipp to go in there and run tests on the magnitude and

35
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:15,680
minitude of the field being generated there at the Bonds of Erotic Polymorphic Experience Motel.

36
00:03:16,320 --> 00:03:22,560
Chipp says it registered at its height 68.2 BLR units of telepathic aura,

37
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:29,040
which only Malapone, among all known telepaths, can produce. The technician finished,

38
00:03:29,040 --> 00:03:35,840
so that's where we stuck Malapone's ident flag on the map, and now he—it—is gone.

39
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:42,800
Did you look on the floor behind the map? It's gone electronically. The man it represents

40
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:47,440
is no longer on Earth, or as far as we can make out on a colony world, either.

41
00:03:48,320 --> 00:03:54,560
Runciter said, I'll consult my dead wife. It's the middle of the night. The moratoriums are closed

42
00:03:54,640 --> 00:04:01,680
now—not in Switzerland, Runciter said, with a grimacing smile, as if some repellent midnight

