67
00:06:22,240 --> 00:06:26,960
Flora, dear, can you hear me? I think I can hear you already. Flora?

68
00:06:27,840 --> 00:06:31,680
When I pass, Herbert Shohenheidt von Vogelsang said to himself,

69
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:38,560
I think I'll reel my ears to revive me one day a century, that way I can observe the fate of all

70
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:45,200
mankind. But that meant a rather high maintenance cost to the heirs, and he knew what that meant.

71
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:51,040
Sooner or later they would rebel, have his body taken out of cold-pack, and, God forbid, buried.

72
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:57,920
Periel is barbaric, Herbert muttered aloud, remnant of the primitive origins of our culture.

73
00:06:58,560 --> 00:07:05,520
Yes, sir, his secretary agreed at her typewriter. In the consultation lounge, several customers

