197
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:13,440
or they don't know. Maybe he thought out to get that Vogelsang creature in here to explain,

198
00:19:13,440 --> 00:19:20,480
maybe something terrible is wrong. Ella, pretty and light-skinned, her eyes, in the days when

199
00:19:20,480 --> 00:19:27,360
they had been open, had been bright and luminous blue. That would not again occur. He could talk to

200
00:19:27,360 --> 00:19:32,560
her and hear her answer, he could communicate with her, but he would never again see her with eyes

201
00:19:32,560 --> 00:19:40,080
opened, nor would her mouth move. She would not smile at his arrival. When he departed, she would not

202
00:19:40,080 --> 00:19:47,760
cry. Is this worth it, he asked himself? Is this better than the old way, the direct road from

203
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:54,480
full life to the grave? I still do have her with me, in a sense, he decided. The alternative

204
00:19:55,040 --> 00:20:05,120
is nothing. In the earphone, words slow and uncertain form, circular thoughts of no importance,

205
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:12,240
fragments of the mysterious dream which she now dwelt in. How did it feel he wondered to be in

206
00:20:12,240 --> 00:20:18,800
Half-Life? He could never fathom it from what Ella had told him, the basis of it, the experience of

207
00:20:18,800 --> 00:20:25,760
it couldn't really be transmitted. Gravity, she had told him once, it begins not to affect you,

208
00:20:25,760 --> 00:20:32,160
and you float more and more. When Half-Life is over, she had said, I think you float out of the

209
00:20:32,160 --> 00:20:39,360
system, out into the stars. But she did not know either, she only wondered and conjectured,

210
00:20:39,360 --> 00:20:43,360
she did not however seem afraid, or unhappy, he felt glad of that.

211
00:20:44,880 --> 00:20:52,960
Hi, Ella, he said clumsily into the microphone. Oh, her answer came, in his ear, she seemed startled,

212
00:20:53,520 --> 00:20:58,400
and yet, of course, her face remained stable, nothing showed. He looked away.

213
00:20:58,560 --> 00:21:05,360
Hello, Glenn. She said, with a sort of childish wonder, surprised, taken aback to find him here.

214
00:21:06,240 --> 00:21:08,000
What? She hesitated.

215
00:21:08,880 --> 00:21:10,320
How much time has passed?

216
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:12,720
Couple years, he said.

217
00:21:13,600 --> 00:21:14,880
Tell me what's going on.

218
00:21:15,920 --> 00:21:22,240
Ah, Christ, he said, everything's going to pieces, the whole organization. That's why I'm here,

219
00:21:22,240 --> 00:21:27,680
you wanted to be brought into major policy planning decisions, and God knows we need that now,

220
00:21:27,680 --> 00:21:31,840
a new policy, or anyhow, a revamping of our scout structure.

221
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:41,680
I was dreaming, Ella said. I saw a smoky red light, a horrible light, and yet I kept

222
00:21:41,680 --> 00:21:43,840
moving toward it, I couldn't stop.

223
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:46,960
Yeah, Runsiter said, nodding.

224
00:21:46,960 --> 00:21:52,400
The bardo told all, the Tibetan Book of the Dead tells about that. You remember reading that,

225
00:21:52,400 --> 00:21:55,600
the doctors made you read it when you were—he hesitated.

226
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:58,000
Dying, he said then.

227
00:21:58,880 --> 00:22:02,240
The smoky red light is bad, isn't it? Ella said.

228
00:22:03,120 --> 00:22:06,880
Yeah, you want to avoid it. He cleared his throat.

229
00:22:07,840 --> 00:22:13,280
Listen, Ella, we've got problems. You feel up to hearing about it? I mean, I don't want to

230
00:22:13,280 --> 00:22:17,360
over-tact you or anything. Just say, if you're too tired, or if there's something else you

231
00:22:17,360 --> 00:22:18,800
want to hear about or discuss.

232
00:22:19,360 --> 00:22:24,800
It's so weird. I think I've been dreaming all this time since you last talked to me.

233
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:32,560
Is it really two years? Do you know, Glen, what I think? I think that other people who are around

234
00:22:32,560 --> 00:22:39,680
me, we seem to be progressively growing together. A lot of my dreams aren't about me at all.

235
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:48,240
Sometimes I'm a man, and sometimes a little boy. Sometimes I'm an old fat woman with varicose veins,

236
00:22:48,880 --> 00:22:52,800
and I'm in places I've never seen doing things that make no sense.

237
00:22:52,960 --> 00:22:59,280
Well, like they say, you're heading for a new womb to be born out of. And that smoky red light,

238
00:22:59,280 --> 00:23:04,960
that's a bad womb. You don't want to go that way. That's a humiliating low sort of womb.

239
00:23:04,960 --> 00:23:09,600
You're probably anticipating your next life for whatever it is.

240
00:23:09,600 --> 00:23:15,360
He felt foolish talking like this. Normally he had no theological convictions,

241
00:23:15,360 --> 00:23:20,960
but the half-life experience was real, and it had made theologians out of all of them.

242
00:23:23,120 --> 00:23:26,640
Hey, he said, changing the subject. Let me tell you what's happened,

243
00:23:26,640 --> 00:23:32,160
what made me come here and bother you. Estol Melopone has dropped out of sight.

244
00:23:33,520 --> 00:23:40,240
A moment of silence, and then Ella laughed. Ha! Who or what is an Estol Melopone?

245
00:23:40,960 --> 00:23:47,840
There can't be any such thing. The laugh, the unique and familiar warmth of it made his spine

246
00:23:47,840 --> 00:23:55,040
tremble. He remembered that about her, even after so many years. He had not heard Ella's laugh

247
00:23:55,040 --> 00:24:03,120
in over a decade. Maybe you've forgotten, he said. Ella said, I haven't forgotten.

248
00:24:03,120 --> 00:24:08,080
I wouldn't forget an Estol Melopone. Ha! Is it like a Hobbit?

249
00:24:09,040 --> 00:24:14,720
It's Raymond Hollis's top telepath. We've had at least one inertial sticking close to him ever

250
00:24:14,720 --> 00:24:20,880
since G.G. Ashwood first scouted him a year and a half ago. We never lose Melopone. We can't afford

251
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:27,200
to. Melopone can, when necessary, generate twice the scyfield of any other Hollis employee.

252
00:24:27,760 --> 00:24:31,360
And Melopone is only one of a whole string of Hollis people who've disappeared.

253
00:24:32,480 --> 00:24:37,600
Anyhow, disappeared as far as we're concerned. As far as all prudent organizations in the

254
00:24:37,600 --> 00:24:43,680
society can make out. So I thought, hell, I'll go ask Ella what's up and what we should do.

255
00:24:43,680 --> 00:24:50,080
Like you specified in your will, remember? I remember. But she sounded remote.

256
00:24:51,040 --> 00:24:56,080
Step up your ads on TV. Warn people. Tell them.

257
00:24:57,760 --> 00:25:00,000
Her voice trailed off into silence then.

258
00:25:01,600 --> 00:25:05,920
This bores you, Runceter said gloomily. No, I—

259
00:25:07,040 --> 00:25:10,000
She hesitated and he felt her once more drift away.

260
00:25:10,240 --> 00:25:15,440
Are they all telepaths? She asked after an interval.

261
00:25:16,400 --> 00:25:22,080
Telepaths and precogs, mostly. They're nowhere on earth. I know that. We've got a dozen

262
00:25:22,080 --> 00:25:26,880
inactive inertials with nothing to do because the size they've been nullifying aren't around.

263
00:25:27,520 --> 00:25:32,240
And what worries me even more, a lot more, is that requests for anti-size have dropped,

264
00:25:32,880 --> 00:25:36,400
which you would expect, given the fact that so many size are missing.

265
00:25:36,400 --> 00:25:42,320
But I know they're on one single project. I mean, I believe. Anyhow, I'm sure of it.

266
00:25:42,320 --> 00:25:47,840
Somebody's hired the bunch of them, but only Hollis knows who it is or where it is,

267
00:25:47,840 --> 00:25:51,840
or what it's all about. He lapsed into brooding silence then.

268
00:25:53,760 --> 00:25:58,640
How would Ella be able to help him figure it out, he asked himself, stuck here in this casket,

269
00:25:58,640 --> 00:26:01,840
frozen out of the world? She knew only what he told her.

270
00:26:02,080 --> 00:26:11,040
Yet he had always relied on her sagacity, that particular female form of it, a wisdom not

271
00:26:11,040 --> 00:26:17,920
based on knowledge or experience, but on something innate. He had not during the period she had lived

272
00:26:17,920 --> 00:26:23,600
been able to fathom it. He certainly could not do so now that she lay in chilled immobility.

273
00:26:24,400 --> 00:26:30,560
Other women he had known, since her death, there had been several, had a little of a trace amounts,

274
00:26:30,560 --> 00:26:37,920
perhaps, intimations of a greater potentiality which in them never emerged as it had in Ella.

275
00:26:39,040 --> 00:26:43,760
Tell me, Ella said, what this melapone person is like?

276
00:26:44,720 --> 00:26:45,680
A screwball.

277
00:26:46,480 --> 00:26:53,200
Working for money or out of conviction. I always feel wary about that, when they have that sigh

278
00:26:53,200 --> 00:27:00,480
mystique, that sense of purpose and cosmic identity, like that awful Serapis had. Remember him?

279
00:27:01,600 --> 00:27:07,360
Serapis isn't around anymore. Hollis allegedly bumped him off because he connived to set up

280
00:27:07,360 --> 00:27:12,240
his own outfit and competition with Hollis. One of his pre-cogs tipped Hollis off.

281
00:27:13,120 --> 00:27:19,440
He added, melapone is much tougher on us than Serapis was. When he's hot, it takes three

282
00:27:19,520 --> 00:27:25,440
inertials to balance his field, and there's no profit in that. We collect, or did collect,

283
00:27:25,440 --> 00:27:31,680
the same fee we get with one inertial. Because the society has a rate schedule now, which we're bound by.

284
00:27:32,400 --> 00:27:38,400
He liked the society less each year. It had become a chronic obsession with him. Its uselessness,

285
00:27:38,400 --> 00:27:45,680
its cost, its vain glory. As near as we can tell, melapone is a money sigh. Does that make you feel

286
00:27:45,680 --> 00:27:50,880
better? Is that less bad? He waited, but heard no response from her.

287
00:27:51,920 --> 00:28:02,720
Ella? He said. Silence. Nervously, he said, Hey, hello there, Ella. Can you hear me? Is something wrong?

288
00:28:03,440 --> 00:28:11,040
Oh, God, he thought she's gone. A pause, and then thoughts materialized in his right ear.

289
00:28:11,040 --> 00:28:18,400
My name is Jory. Not Ella's thoughts, a different Elan, more vital and yet clumsier,

290
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:19,840
without her deft subtlety.

291
00:28:20,720 --> 00:28:25,120
Get off the line, Runceter said in panic. I was talking to my wife, Ella. Where'd you come from?

292
00:28:25,760 --> 00:28:31,200
I am Jory, the thoughts came, and no one talks to me. I'd like to visit with you a while, Mr.,

293
00:28:31,200 --> 00:28:35,040
if that's okay with you. What's your name? Stammering, Runceter said.

294
00:28:36,000 --> 00:28:41,840
I want my wife, Mrs. Ella Runceter. I paid to talk to her, and that's who I want to talk to, not you.

295
00:28:42,400 --> 00:28:47,280
I know Mrs. Runceter. The thoughts clanged in his ear, much stronger now. She talks to me,

296
00:28:47,280 --> 00:28:52,400
but it isn't the same as somebody like you talking to me, somebody in the world. Mrs. Runceter is here

297
00:28:52,400 --> 00:28:58,720
where we are. Doesn't count, because she doesn't know any more than we do. What year is it, Mr.?

298
00:28:58,720 --> 00:29:03,360
Did they send that big ship to Proxima? I'm very interested in that. Maybe you can tell me.

299
00:29:03,360 --> 00:29:05,920
And if you want, I can tell Mrs. Runceter later on, okay?

300
00:29:07,200 --> 00:29:12,400
Runceter popped the plug from his ear, hurriedly set down the earphone and the rest of the gadgetry.

301
00:29:12,400 --> 00:29:18,400
He left the stale, dust-saturated office and roamed about among the chilling caskets row after row,

302
00:29:18,400 --> 00:29:24,160
all of them neatly arranged by number. Moratorium employees swam up before him and then vanished

303
00:29:24,160 --> 00:29:29,680
as he churned on, searching for the owner. Is something the matter, Mr.? Runceter?

304
00:29:29,760 --> 00:29:33,760
The Von Vogel Sang person said, observing him as he floundered about,

305
00:29:33,760 --> 00:29:40,720
can I assist you? I got some thing coming in over the wire, Runceter panted, halting,

306
00:29:40,720 --> 00:29:46,160
instead of Ella. Damn you guys and your shoddy business practices! This shouldn't happen. And

307
00:29:46,160 --> 00:29:51,280
what does it mean? He followed after the moratorium owner who had already started in the direction

308
00:29:51,280 --> 00:29:57,680
of Office 2A. If I ran my business this way, did the individual identify himself?

309
00:29:57,680 --> 00:30:03,360
Yeah, he called himself Jory. Frowning with obvious worry, Von Vogel Sang said,

310
00:30:03,920 --> 00:30:10,480
that would be Jory Miller. I believe he's located next to your wife in the bin. But I can see it's Ella.

311
00:30:11,520 --> 00:30:18,560
After prolonged proximity, Von Vogel Sang explained, there is occasionally a mutual osmosis,

312
00:30:18,560 --> 00:30:25,680
a suffusion between the mentalities of half-lifers. Jory Miller's cephalic activity is particularly

313
00:30:25,680 --> 00:30:32,400
good. Your wife's is not. That makes for an unfortunately one-way passage of protophasons.

314
00:30:33,040 --> 00:30:38,960
Can you correct it? Runceter asked hoarsely. He found himself still, spent still, panting and

315
00:30:38,960 --> 00:30:46,560
shaking. Get that thing out of my wife's mind and get her back. That's your job! Von Vogel

316
00:30:46,560 --> 00:30:54,080
Sang said in a stilted voice, if this condition persists, your money will be returned to you.

317
00:30:54,080 --> 00:30:59,840
Who cares about the money? Snot the money! They had reached Office 2A now. Runceter

318
00:30:59,840 --> 00:31:04,240
unsteadily reseeded himself, his heart laboring so that he could hardly speak.

319
00:31:04,800 --> 00:31:09,680
If you don't get this Jory person off the line, he half gasped, half snarled,

320
00:31:09,680 --> 00:31:16,320
I'll sue you! I'll close down this place! Facing the casket Von Vogel Sang pressed the

321
00:31:16,320 --> 00:31:23,120
