557
00:54:36,560 --> 00:54:40,160
I can read your mind, G.G. said to her, looking a little nettle.

558
00:54:40,160 --> 00:54:43,440
I know you can change the past. You've done it. Pat said,

559
00:54:44,400 --> 00:54:50,480
I can change the past, but I don't go into the past. I don't time travel, as you want your

560
00:54:50,480 --> 00:54:59,920
tester to think. How do you change the past, Joe asked her. I think about it. One specific

561
00:54:59,920 --> 00:55:05,680
aspect of it, such as one incident or something somebody said, or a little thing that

562
00:55:05,680 --> 00:55:11,200
happened that I wish hadn't happened. The first time I did this, as a child, when she was six

563
00:55:11,200 --> 00:55:15,280
years old, G.G. broke in, living in Detroit with her parents, of course, she broke a ceramic

564
00:55:15,280 --> 00:55:20,880
