4719
06:20:09,440 --> 06:20:15,600
Tomorrow, Runceter promised, after I get some sleep. This is damn near finished me off.

4720
06:20:16,720 --> 06:20:20,720
This loss of all my best people, he said to himself, especially Joe Chip.

4721
06:20:21,440 --> 06:20:26,720
My organization is depleted, and we won't be able to resume commercial operations for months,

4722
06:20:26,720 --> 06:20:32,400
maybe years. God, he thought, where am I going to get inertials to replace those I've lost,

4723
06:20:32,400 --> 06:20:38,080
and where am I going to find a tester like Joe? Niggleman said, sure, Glenn, get a good night's

4724
06:20:38,080 --> 06:20:42,160
sleep, and then meet me in my office tomorrow, say, at ten o'clock our time.

4725
06:20:42,800 --> 06:20:49,680
Thanks, Runceter said. He rang off, then threw himself heavily down on a pink plastic couch

4726
06:20:49,680 --> 06:20:55,360
across the corridor from the phone. I can't find a tester like Joe, he said to himself.

4727
06:20:56,160 --> 06:21:00,240
The fact of the matter is that Runceter Associates is finished.

4728
06:21:01,600 --> 06:21:06,480
The moratorium owner came in, then, putting in another of his untimely appearances.

4729
06:21:07,040 --> 06:21:12,080
Can I get you anything, Mr. Runceter, a cup of coffee? Another amphetamine? Perhaps a

4730
06:21:12,080 --> 06:21:18,080
twelve-hour spanthule? In my office I have some twenty-four-hour spanthules. One of those would

4731
06:21:18,080 --> 06:21:24,640
get you back up into action for hours, if not all night. All night, Runceter said, I intend to sleep.

4732
06:21:25,280 --> 06:21:32,000
Then how about a flap away, Runceter grated. The moratorium owner scuttled off, leaving him alone.

4733
06:21:32,960 --> 06:21:39,040
Why did I have to pick this place, Runceter asked himself. I guess because Ella's here,

4734
06:21:39,040 --> 06:21:42,880
it is, after all, the best. That's why she's here, and hence why they're all here.

4735
06:21:43,040 --> 06:21:49,760
Think of them, he reflected, so many who were so recently on this side of the casket,

4736
06:21:49,760 --> 06:21:57,280
what a catastrophe. Ella, he said to himself, remembering, I better talk to her again for

4737
06:21:57,280 --> 06:22:02,240
a moment to let her know how things are going. That's after all what I told her I'd do.

4738
06:22:03,440 --> 06:22:06,720
Getting to his feet, he started off in search of the moratorium owner.

4739
06:22:07,680 --> 06:22:11,840
Am I going to get that damn jury this time? He asked himself.

4740
06:22:12,320 --> 06:22:15,840
Will I be able to keep Ella in focus long enough to tell her what Joe said?

4741
06:22:15,840 --> 06:22:22,080
It's become so hard to hang on to her now, with Jory growing and expanding and feeding on her,

4742
06:22:22,080 --> 06:22:27,360
and maybe on others over there in Half-Life. The moratorium should do something about him.

4743
06:22:27,360 --> 06:22:32,320
Jory's a hazard to everyone here. Why did they let him go on? He asked himself.

4744
06:22:33,280 --> 06:22:40,080
He thought, maybe because they can't stop him. Maybe there's never been anyone in Half-Life

4745
06:22:40,080 --> 06:22:45,200
like Jory before. 15.

4746
06:22:47,120 --> 06:22:51,840
Could it be that I have bad breath, Tom? Well, Ed, if you're worried about that,

4747
06:22:51,840 --> 06:22:55,920
try today's new U-BIC with powerful germicidal foaming action,

4748
06:22:55,920 --> 06:22:58,560
guaranteed safe when taken as directed.

4749
06:22:58,800 --> 06:23:01,120
16.

4750
06:23:01,120 --> 06:23:04,480
The door of the ancient hotel room swung open. Don Denny,

4751
06:23:04,480 --> 06:23:09,120
accompanied by a middle-aged, responsible-looking man with neatly trimmed gray hair, entered.

4752
06:23:09,760 --> 06:23:12,880
Denny, his face strained with apprehension, said,

4753
06:23:12,880 --> 06:23:16,640
How are you, Joe? Why aren't you lying down? For Christ's sake, get on to the bed.

4754
06:23:17,440 --> 06:23:22,720
Please lie down, Mr. Chip, the doctor said, as he set his medical bag on the vanity table

4755
06:23:22,720 --> 06:23:28,080
and opened it up. Is there pain along with the innovation and the difficult respiration?

4756
06:23:28,720 --> 06:23:32,800
He approached the bed with an old-fashioned stethoscope and cumbersome blood-pressure

4757
06:23:32,800 --> 06:23:38,400
reading equipment. Do you have any history of cardiac involvement, Mr. Chip, or your

4758
06:23:38,400 --> 06:23:43,360
mother or father? Unbutton your shirt, please. He drew up a wooden chair beside the bed,

4759
06:23:43,360 --> 06:23:48,000
seated himself expectantly on it. Joe said, I'm okay now.

4760
06:23:48,960 --> 06:23:51,440
Let him listen to your heart, Denny said, tersely.

4761
06:23:52,160 --> 06:23:55,920
Okay. Joe stretched out on the bed and unbuttoned his shirt.

4762
06:23:56,720 --> 06:23:59,600
Runseter managed to get through to me, he said to Denny.

4763
06:24:00,240 --> 06:24:04,320
We're in cold pack. He's on the other side, trying to reach us.

4764
06:24:05,120 --> 06:24:11,440
Someone else is trying to injure us. Pat didn't do it, or anyhow, she didn't do it alone. Neither

4765
06:24:11,440 --> 06:24:16,320
she nor Runseter knows what's going on. When you opened the door, did you see Runseter?

4766
06:24:17,040 --> 06:24:21,680
No, Denny said. He was sitting across the room from me, Joe said, two, three minutes ago.

4767
06:24:22,400 --> 06:24:25,440
Sorry, Joe, he said, that was the last thing he said to me.

4768
06:24:26,080 --> 06:24:30,400
And then he cut contact, stopped communicating, just cancelled himself out.

4769
06:24:31,200 --> 06:24:34,000
Look on the vanity table and see if he left the spray can of Eubach.

4770
06:24:34,880 --> 06:24:37,840
Denny searched, then held up the brightly illuminated can.

4771
06:24:38,640 --> 06:24:41,360
Here it is, but it seems empty. Denny shook it.

4772
06:24:42,080 --> 06:24:44,160
Almost empty, Joe said.

4773
06:24:44,800 --> 06:24:48,720
Spray what's left on yourself. Go ahead. He gestured emphatically.

4774
06:24:49,360 --> 06:24:53,520
Don't talk, Mr. Chip, the doctor said, listening to his stethoscope.

4775
06:24:53,520 --> 06:24:57,920
He then rolled up Joe's sleeve and began winding inflatable rubber fabric around

4776
06:24:57,920 --> 06:25:00,240
his arm in preparation for the blood pressure test.

4777
06:25:01,280 --> 06:25:02,880
How's my heart, Joe asked.

4778
06:25:03,440 --> 06:25:07,600
It appears normal, the doctor said, although slightly fast.

4779
06:25:08,320 --> 06:25:10,640
See, Joe said to Don Denny, I've recovered.

4780
06:25:11,440 --> 06:25:14,560
Denny said, the others are dying, Joe.

4781
06:25:15,520 --> 06:25:17,600
Half sitting up, Joe said, all of them?

4782
06:25:18,240 --> 06:25:21,520
Everyone that's left. He held the can, but did not use it.

4783
06:25:22,480 --> 06:25:24,080
Pat too, Joe asked.

4784
06:25:24,960 --> 06:25:28,320
When I got out of the elevator on the second floor here, I found her.

4785
06:25:28,320 --> 06:25:31,600
It had just begun to hit her. She seemed terribly surprised.

4786
06:25:31,600 --> 06:25:34,720
Apparently she couldn't believe it. He set the can down again.

4787
06:25:35,440 --> 06:25:38,080
I guess she thought she was doing it, with her talent.

4788
06:25:39,040 --> 06:25:41,120
Joe said, that's right, that's what she thought.

4789
06:25:41,840 --> 06:25:43,120
Why won't she use the Eubach?

4790
06:25:43,920 --> 06:25:46,720
Hell, Joe, we're going to die. You know it and I know it.

4791
06:25:47,680 --> 06:25:50,640
He removed his horn-rimmed glasses and rubbed his eyes.

4792
06:25:51,600 --> 06:25:56,720
After I saw Pat's condition, I went into the other rooms and that's when I saw the rest of them.

4793
06:25:56,720 --> 06:26:01,360
Of us. That's why we took so long getting here. I had Dr. Taylor examine them.

4794
06:26:02,000 --> 06:26:07,600
I couldn't believe they dwindle away so fast. The acceleration has been so goddamn great

4795
06:26:07,600 --> 06:26:08,800
in just the last hour.

4796
06:26:09,440 --> 06:26:12,000
Use the Eubach, Joe said, or I'll use it on you.

4797
06:26:12,960 --> 06:26:17,200
Don Denny again picked up the can, again shook it, pointed the nozzle toward himself.

4798
06:26:17,840 --> 06:26:22,800
All right, he said, if that's what you want, there really isn't any reason not to. This is the end,

4799
06:26:22,800 --> 06:26:27,040
isn't it? I mean, they're all dead. Only you and I are left and the Eubach is going to wear

4800
06:26:27,040 --> 06:26:30,800
off you in a few hours and you won't be able to get any more, which will leave me.

4801
06:26:32,000 --> 06:26:35,120
His decision made Denny depress the button of the spray can.

4802
06:26:35,680 --> 06:26:40,080
The shimmering, palpitating vapor filled with particles of metallic light that danced

4803
06:26:40,080 --> 06:26:46,000
nimbly formed at once around him. Don Denny disappeared, concealed by the nimbus of radiant

4804
06:26:46,000 --> 06:26:52,400
ergic excitement. Pausing in his task of reading Joe's blood pressure, Dr. Taylor twisted his

4805
06:26:52,400 --> 06:26:57,840
head to see both he and Joe watched as the vapor now condensed, puddles of it glistened on the

4806
06:26:57,840 --> 06:27:01,920
carpet and down the wall behind Denny it drizzled in bright streaks.

4807
06:27:03,840 --> 06:27:09,920
The cloud concealing Denny evaporated. The person standing there, in the center

4808
06:27:09,920 --> 06:27:16,400
of the vaporizing stain of Eubach that had saturated the worn and dingy carpet, was not Don Denny.

4809
06:27:17,920 --> 06:27:23,600
An adolescent boy, mawkishly slender with irregular black button eyes beneath tangled

4810
06:27:23,600 --> 06:27:30,480
brows. He wore an anachronistic costume, white drip dry shirt, jeans and laceless leather slippers,

4811
06:27:31,040 --> 06:27:36,320
clothes from the middle of the century. On his elongated face Joe saw a smile, but it was a

4812
06:27:36,320 --> 06:27:43,520
misshapen smile, a thwarted crease that became now almost a jeering lear. No two features matched,

4813
06:27:43,520 --> 06:27:47,440
his ears had too many convolutions in them to fit with his chitinous eyes.

4814
06:27:48,160 --> 06:27:54,400
His straight hair contradicted the interwoven curly bristles of his brows and his nose, Joe thought,

4815
06:27:54,400 --> 06:28:00,160
too thin, too sharp, far too long. Even his chin failed to harmonize with the balance of his face.

4816
06:28:00,720 --> 06:28:06,240
It had a deep chisel mark in it, a cleft, obviously penetrating far up into the bone,

4817
06:28:06,480 --> 06:28:12,480
Joe thought as if at that point the manufacturer of this creature struck at a blow aimed at obliterating

4818
06:28:12,480 --> 06:28:18,320
it. But the physical material, the base substance, had been too dense. The boy had not fractured and

4819
06:28:18,320 --> 06:28:24,400
split apart. He existed in defiance of even the force that had constructed him. He jeered at

4820
06:28:24,400 --> 06:28:33,440
everything else and it, too. Who are you? Joe said. The boy's fingers writhed, a twitch protecting

4821
06:28:33,520 --> 06:28:39,840
him evidently from a stammer. Sometimes I call myself Matt and sometimes Bill, he said,

4822
06:28:39,840 --> 06:28:48,880
but mostly I'm Jory. That's my real name, Jory. Gray, shabby teeth showed as he spoke, and a grubby tongue.

4823
06:28:51,120 --> 06:28:56,400
After an interval, Joe said, where's Denny? He never came into this room did he?

4824
06:28:57,360 --> 06:29:03,280
Dead, he thought, with the others. I ate Denny a long time ago. The boy, Jory, said,

4825
06:29:03,520 --> 06:29:08,080
right at the beginning, before they came here from New York, first day, Wendy Wright, then he came second.

4826
06:29:09,040 --> 06:29:15,360
Joe said, how do you mean eight? Literally, he wondered his flesh undulating with a version.

4827
06:29:15,360 --> 06:29:20,400
The gross physical motion rolled through him and golfing him as if his body wanted to shrink away,

4828
06:29:20,400 --> 06:29:26,240
however he managed more or less to conceal it. I did what I do, Jory said. It's hard to explain,

4829
06:29:26,240 --> 06:29:31,440
but I've been doing it a long time to lots of half-life people. I eat their life, what remains

4830
06:29:31,440 --> 06:29:36,240
of it. There's very little in each person, so I need a lot of them. I used to wait until they had

4831
06:29:36,240 --> 06:29:40,800
been in half-life a while, but now I have to have them immediately if I'm going to be able to live

4832
06:29:40,800 --> 06:29:46,480
myself. If you come close to me and listen, I'll hold my mouth open. You can hear their voices.

4833
06:29:47,200 --> 06:29:50,560
Not all of them, but anyhow the last ones I ate, the ones you know.

4834
06:29:51,520 --> 06:29:57,120
With his fingernail he picked at an upper incisor. His head tilted on one side as he regarded Joe,

4835
06:29:57,120 --> 06:30:01,600
evidently waiting to hear his reaction. Don't you have anything to say? He said.

4836
06:30:02,480 --> 06:30:08,640
It was you who started me dying down there in the lobby. Me and not Pat. I ate her out in the

4837
06:30:08,640 --> 06:30:13,520
hall by the elevator, and then I ate the others. I thought you were dead. He rotated the can of

4838
06:30:13,520 --> 06:30:19,040
Hubek, which he still held. I can't figure this out. What's in it? And where does Ranseter get it?

4839
06:30:19,040 --> 06:30:24,800
He's scald. But Ranseter can't be doing it. You're right. He's on the outside. This originates from

4840
06:30:24,800 --> 06:30:29,600
within our environment. It has to, because nothing can come in from outside except words.

4841
06:30:30,560 --> 06:30:36,480
Joe said, So there's nothing you can do to me. You can't eat me because of the Hubek. I can't

4842
06:30:36,480 --> 06:30:41,520
eat you for a while, but the Hubek will wear off. You don't know that. You don't even know what it is,

4843
06:30:41,520 --> 06:30:49,280
or where it comes from. I wonder if I can kill you, he thought. The boy, Jory, seemed delicate.

4844
06:30:50,000 --> 06:30:54,480
This is the thing that got Wendy, he said to himself. I'm seeing it, face to face,

4845
06:30:54,480 --> 06:31:00,240
as I knew I eventually would. Wendy, Al, the real Don Denny, all the rest of them.

4846
06:31:00,240 --> 06:31:04,560
It even ate Ranseter's corpse as it lay in the casket at the mortuary. There must have been a

4847
06:31:04,560 --> 06:31:09,680
flicker of residual proto-phasic activity in or near it or something, anyhow, which attracted him.

4848
06:31:10,480 --> 06:31:15,440
The doctor said, Mr. Chip, I didn't have a chance to finish taking your blood pressure.

4849
06:31:15,440 --> 06:31:19,440
Please lie back down. Joe stared at him, then said,

4850
06:31:20,400 --> 06:31:23,520
Didn't he see you change, Jory? Hasn't he heard what you've been saying?

4851
06:31:24,240 --> 06:31:29,440
Dr. Taylor is a product of my mind, Jory said, like every other fixture in this pseudo-world.

4852
06:31:30,320 --> 06:31:34,000
I don't believe it, Joe said. To the doctor, he said,

4853
06:31:34,000 --> 06:31:40,480
You heard what he's been saying, didn't you? With a hollow whistling pop, the doctor disappeared.

4854
06:31:41,280 --> 06:31:43,440
See? Jory said, pleased.

4855
06:31:44,480 --> 06:31:47,440
What are you going to do when I'm killed off? Joe asked the boy.

4856
06:31:47,440 --> 06:31:52,080
Will you keep on maintaining this 1939 world, this pseudo-world, as you call it?

4857
06:31:52,080 --> 06:31:57,840
Of course not. There'd be no reason to. Then it's all for me. Just for me, this entire world.

4858
06:31:59,040 --> 06:32:03,760
Jory said, It's not very large. One hotel in Des Moines, and a street outside the window with a

4859
06:32:03,760 --> 06:32:07,920
few people and cars, and maybe a couple of other buildings thrown in, stores across the street

4860
06:32:07,920 --> 06:32:13,680
for you to look at when you happen to see out. So you're not maintaining any New York or Zurich,

4861
06:32:13,680 --> 06:32:17,600
or why should I? No one's there. Wherever you and the others of the group went,

4862
06:32:17,600 --> 06:32:21,360
I constructed a tangible reality corresponding to their minimal expectations.

4863
06:32:22,240 --> 06:32:26,720
When you flew here from New York, I created hundreds of miles of countryside, town after town.

4864
06:32:27,680 --> 06:32:31,840
I found that very exhausting. I had to eat a great deal to make up for that. In fact,

4865
06:32:31,840 --> 06:32:35,920
that's the reason I had to finish off the others so soon after you got here. I needed to replenish

4866
06:32:35,920 --> 06:32:45,440
myself. Joe said, Why 1939? Why not our own contemporary world, 1992? The effort! I can't

4867
06:32:45,440 --> 06:32:52,000
keep objects from regressing. Doing it all alone, it was too much for me. I created 1992 at first,

4868
06:32:52,000 --> 06:32:57,600
but then things began to break down. The coins, the cream, the cigarettes, all those phenomena

4869
06:32:57,600 --> 06:33:01,120
that you noticed, and then runs to the keep breaking through from outside. That made it

4870
06:33:01,120 --> 06:33:04,800
even harder for me. Actually, it would have been better if he hadn't interfered.

4871
06:33:05,600 --> 06:33:11,920
Jory grin slighly. But I didn't worry about the reversion. I knew you'd figure it was Pat Conley.

4872
06:33:12,480 --> 06:33:16,880
It would seem like her talent because it's sort of like what her talent does. I thought maybe the

4873
06:33:16,880 --> 06:33:21,120
rest of you would kill her. I would enjoy that. His grin increased.

4874
06:33:22,080 --> 06:33:27,040
What's the point of keeping this hotel and the street outside going for me now? Joe said.

4875
06:33:27,840 --> 06:33:32,720
Now that I know. But I always do it this way. Jory's eyes widened.

4876
06:33:32,960 --> 06:33:41,120
Joe said, I'm going to kill you. He stepped toward Jory in an uncoordinated half-falling motion.

4877
06:33:41,120 --> 06:33:45,280
Raising his open hands, he plunged against the boy, trying to capture the neck, searching for

4878
06:33:45,280 --> 06:33:51,840
the bent pipe stem windpipe with all his fingers. Snarling, Jory bit him. The great shoveled teeth

4879
06:33:51,840 --> 06:33:56,240
fastened deep into Joe's right hand. They hung on as meanwhile Jory raised his head,

4880
06:33:56,240 --> 06:34:02,080
lifting Joe's hand with his jaw. Jory stared at him with unwinking eyes, snoring wetly as he

4881
06:34:02,080 --> 06:34:07,040
tried to close his jaws. The teeth sank deeper and Joe felt the pain of it throughout him.

4882
06:34:07,040 --> 06:34:13,200
He's eating me, he realized. You can't, he said aloud. He hit Jory on the snout, punching again

4883
06:34:13,200 --> 06:34:18,800
and again. You bit keeps you away, he said, as he cuffed Jory's jeering eyes. You can't do it to me.

4884
06:34:20,720 --> 06:34:26,080
Jory bubbled, working his jaws sideways like a sheep's, grinding Joe's hand until the pain

4885
06:34:26,080 --> 06:34:31,680
became too much for Joe to stand. He kicked Jory. The teeth released his hand. He crept backward,

4886
06:34:31,760 --> 06:34:35,200
looking at the blood rising from the punctures made by the troll teeth.

4887
06:34:35,200 --> 06:34:41,200
Jesus, he said to himself, appalled. You can't do to me, Joe said, what you did to them.

4888
06:34:41,920 --> 06:34:45,680
Locating the spray can of Eubach, he pointed the nozzle toward the bleeding wound which

4889
06:34:45,680 --> 06:34:51,040
his hand had become. He pressed the red plastic stud and a weak stream of particles emerged and

4890
06:34:51,040 --> 06:34:57,120
settled in a film over the chewed torn flesh. The pain immediately departed before his eyes,

4891
06:34:57,120 --> 06:35:02,160
the wound healed. And you can't kill me, Jory said. He still grinned.

4892
06:35:03,200 --> 06:35:09,360
Joe said, I'm going downstairs. He walked unsteadily to the door of the room and opened it.

4893
06:35:09,360 --> 06:35:15,520
Outside lay the dingy hall. He started forward, step by step treading carefully. The floor,

4894
06:35:15,520 --> 06:35:19,360
however, seemed substantial, not a quasi or a real world at all.

4895
06:35:20,080 --> 06:35:25,040
Don't go too far, Jory said from behind him. I can't keep too great an area going. Like,

4896
06:35:25,040 --> 06:35:28,640
if you were going to get into one of those cars and drive for miles, eventually you'd reach a

4897
06:35:28,640 --> 06:35:32,000
point where it breaks down and you wouldn't like that any better than I do.

4898
06:35:32,640 --> 06:35:37,200
I don't see what I have to lose. Joe reached the elevator, pressed the down button.

4899
06:35:37,200 --> 06:35:40,720
Jory called after him. I have trouble with elevators. They're complicated. Maybe you should

4900
06:35:40,720 --> 06:35:47,200
take the stairs. After waiting a little longer, Joe gave up. As Jory had advised, he descended

4901
06:35:47,200 --> 06:35:53,120
by the stairs, the same flight up which he had so recently come step by step in an agony of effort.

4902
06:35:53,360 --> 06:36:01,200
Well, he thought. That's one of the two agencies who are at work. Jory is the one who's destroying

4903
06:36:01,200 --> 06:36:07,120
us, has destroyed us, except for me. Behind Jory there is nothing. He is the end.

4904
06:36:08,000 --> 06:36:13,840
Will I meet the other? Probably not soon enough for it to matter, he decided. He looked once more

4905
06:36:13,840 --> 06:36:18,560
at his hand completely well. Reaching the lobby, he gazed around him at the people, the great

4906
06:36:18,640 --> 06:36:24,800
chandelier overhead. Jory, in many respects, had done a good job, despite the reversion to these

4907
06:36:24,800 --> 06:36:30,560
older forms. Real, he thought, experiencing the floor beneath his feet. I can't get over it.

4908
06:36:32,080 --> 06:36:37,120
He thought, Jory must have had experience. He must have done this many times before.

4909
06:36:38,000 --> 06:36:40,000
Going to the hotel desk, he said to the clerk,

4910
06:36:40,640 --> 06:36:42,800
You have a restaurant that you'd recommend?

4911
06:36:43,440 --> 06:36:47,440
Down the street, the clerk said, pausing in his task of sorting mail.

4912
06:36:47,440 --> 06:36:50,720
To your right, the matador, you'll find it excellent, sir.

4913
06:36:52,080 --> 06:36:58,000
I'm lonely, Joe said on impulse. Does the hotel have any source of supply, any girls?

4914
06:36:58,800 --> 06:37:04,320
The clerk said in a clipped disapproving voice, Not this hotel, sir. This hotel does not pander.

4915
06:37:05,040 --> 06:37:09,520
You keep a good clean family, hotel, Joe said. We like to think so, sir.

4916
06:37:10,080 --> 06:37:15,200
I was just testing you, Joe said. I wanted to be sure what kind of hotel I was staying in.

4917
06:37:15,920 --> 06:37:20,000
He left the counter, recrossed the lobby, made his way down the wide marble stairs,

4918
06:37:20,000 --> 06:37:23,200
through the revolving door, and onto the pavement outside.

4919
06:37:26,480 --> 06:37:32,960
16. Wake up to a hearty, lip-smacking bowl full of nutritious, nourishing,

4920
06:37:32,960 --> 06:37:39,200
ubic toasted flakes, the adult cereal that's more crunchy, more tasty, more mmmish,

4921
06:37:39,760 --> 06:37:46,320
ubic breakfast cereal, the whole bowl taste treat, do not exceed recommended portion at any one meal.

4922
06:37:48,560 --> 06:37:54,400
The diversity of cars impressed him. Many years represented many makes and many models.

4923
06:37:54,960 --> 06:37:59,360
The fact that they mostly came in black could not be laid at Jory's door. This detail was authentic.

4924
06:38:00,240 --> 06:38:08,720
But how did Jory know it? That's peculiar, he thought. Jory's knowledge of the minutiae of 1939,

4925
06:38:08,720 --> 06:38:15,280
a period in which none of us lived, except Glenn Runceter. Then all at once he realized why.

4926
06:38:16,160 --> 06:38:22,880
Jory had told the truth. He had constructed not this world, but the world, or rather its

4927
06:38:22,880 --> 06:38:29,520
phantasmagoric counterpart of their own time. Decomposition back to these forms was not of

4928
06:38:29,520 --> 06:38:36,080
his doing. They happened despite his efforts. These are natural atavisms, Joe realized,

4929
06:38:36,080 --> 06:38:42,160
happening mechanically as Jory's strength wanes. As the boy says, it's an enormous effort.

4930
06:38:42,160 --> 06:38:47,520
This is perhaps the first time he has created a world this diverse for so many people at once.

4931
06:38:47,520 --> 06:38:50,400
It isn't usual for so many half-lifers to be interwired.

4932
06:38:51,280 --> 06:38:56,560
We have put an abnormal strain on Jory, he said to himself, and we paid for it.

4933
06:38:57,600 --> 06:39:02,960
A square old dodged taxi, spotted past Joe, waved at it, and the cab floundered noisily to the curb.

4934
06:39:03,760 --> 06:39:09,920
Let's test out what Jory said, he said to himself, as to the early boundary of this quasi-world now.

4935
06:39:10,720 --> 06:39:11,760
To the driver, he said,

4936
06:39:12,720 --> 06:39:16,800
Take me for a ride through town, go anywhere you want. I'd like to see as many streets and

4937
06:39:16,800 --> 06:39:21,120
buildings and people as possible. And then when you've driven through all of Des Moines,

4938
06:39:21,120 --> 06:39:24,000
I want you to drive me to the next town, and we'll see that.

4939
06:39:24,720 --> 06:39:29,680
I don't go between towns, Mr. the driver said, holding the door open for Joe,

4940
06:39:29,680 --> 06:39:35,280
but I'll be glad to drive you around Des Moines. It's a nice city, sir. You've not stayed, aren't you?

4941
06:39:35,840 --> 06:39:40,640
New York, Joe said, getting inside the cab. The cab rolled back out into traffic.

4942
06:39:42,160 --> 06:39:47,760
How did they feel about the war back in New York, the driver asked presently. Do you think we'll

4943
06:39:47,760 --> 06:39:54,320
be getting into it? Rosa wants to get us. I don't care to discuss politics or the war, Joe said harshly.

4944
06:39:55,280 --> 06:40:00,640
They drove for a time in silence. Watching the buildings, people, and cars go by,

4945
06:40:00,640 --> 06:40:06,000
Joe asked himself again how Jory could maintain it all so many details, he marveled.

4946
06:40:06,720 --> 06:40:10,160
I should be coming to the edge of it soon. It has to be just about now.

4947
06:40:10,320 --> 06:40:15,520
"'Driver,' he said, are there any houses of prostitution here in Des Moines?'

4948
06:40:16,080 --> 06:40:17,520
"'No,' the driver said.

4949
06:40:18,480 --> 06:40:24,000
Maybe Jory can't manage that, Joe reflected, because of his youth, or maybe he disapproves.

4950
06:40:24,880 --> 06:40:26,720
He felt all at once tired.

4951
06:40:27,520 --> 06:40:30,240
"'Where am I going?' he asked himself, and what for?'

4952
06:40:30,960 --> 06:40:36,400
To prove to myself that what Jory told me is true. I already know it's true. I saw the doctor wink out.

4953
06:40:36,960 --> 06:40:40,480
I saw Jory emerge from inside Don Denny. That should have been enough.

4954
06:40:41,040 --> 06:40:45,760
All I'm doing this way is putting more of a load on Jory, which will increase his appetite.

4955
06:40:46,480 --> 06:40:49,120
"'I'd better give up,' he decided. This is pointless.'

4956
06:40:50,560 --> 06:40:54,000
And, as Jory had said, the uber would be wearing off anyhow.

4957
06:40:54,720 --> 06:40:59,600
This driving around Des Moines is not the way I want to spend my last minutes or hours of life.

4958
06:40:59,600 --> 06:41:01,040
There must be something else.'

4959
06:41:02,000 --> 06:41:07,760
Along the sidewalk a girl moved in a slow, easy gate. She seemed to be window-shopping,

4960
06:41:07,760 --> 06:41:12,960
a pretty girl, with gay blonde pigtails, wearing an unbuttoned sweater over her blouse,

4961
06:41:12,960 --> 06:41:15,520
a bright red skirt, and high-heeled little shoes.

4962
06:41:16,400 --> 06:41:20,640
"'Slow the cab,' he instructed the driver. There, by that girl with the pigtails.

4963
06:41:21,200 --> 06:41:23,360
"'She won't talk to you,' the driver said.

4964
06:41:23,360 --> 06:41:25,280
"'She'll call a cop.' Joe said.

4965
06:41:25,840 --> 06:41:28,560
"'I don't care.' It hardly mattered at this point.

4966
06:41:29,280 --> 06:41:32,000
Slowing the old dodge bumbled its way to the curb.

4967
06:41:32,000 --> 06:41:36,000
Its tires protested as they rubbed against the curb. The girl glanced up.

4968
06:41:36,720 --> 06:41:38,320
"'Hi, Miss,' Joe said.

4969
06:41:39,280 --> 06:41:44,720
She regarded him with curiosity. Her warm, intelligent blue eyes widened a little,

4970
06:41:44,720 --> 06:41:49,360
but they showed no aversion or alarm. Rather, she seemed slightly amused at him,

4971
06:41:49,360 --> 06:41:50,480
but in a friendly way.

4972
06:41:51,360 --> 06:41:52,640
"'Yes,' she said.

4973
06:41:53,600 --> 06:41:55,840
"'I'm going to die,' Joe said.

4974
06:41:56,560 --> 06:41:59,040
"'Oh, dear,' the girl said with concern.

4975
06:41:59,680 --> 06:42:00,400
"'Are you—'

4976
06:42:00,400 --> 06:42:02,800
"'He's not sick,' the driver put in.

4977
06:42:02,800 --> 06:42:05,200
He's been asking after girls. He just wants to pick you up.'

4978
06:42:06,000 --> 06:42:10,400
The girl laughed, without hostility, and she did not depart.

4979
06:42:11,680 --> 06:42:14,880
"'It's almost dinner time,' Joe said to her.

4980
06:42:14,880 --> 06:42:18,720
"'Let me take you to a restaurant. The matador, I understand that's nice.'

4981
06:42:19,680 --> 06:42:23,360
His tiredness now had increased. He felt the weight of it on him.

4982
06:42:23,920 --> 06:42:29,280
And then he realized, with muted, weary horror, that it consisted of the same fatigue

4983
06:42:29,280 --> 06:42:33,520
which had attacked him in the hotel lobby after he had shown the police citation to Pat.

4984
06:42:34,400 --> 06:42:35,520
And the cold—'

4985
06:42:36,480 --> 06:42:41,040
Stealthily, the physical experience of the cold pack surrounding him had come back.

4986
06:42:41,680 --> 06:42:44,560
The u-bick is beginning to wear off,' he realized.

4987
06:42:45,120 --> 06:42:46,160
"'I don't have much longer.'

4988
06:42:46,240 --> 06:42:51,360
Something must have showed in his face. The girl walked toward him up to the window of the cab.

4989
06:42:51,360 --> 06:42:53,520
"'Are you all right?' she asked.

4990
06:42:54,160 --> 06:42:55,440
Joe said with effort.

4991
06:42:56,320 --> 06:42:57,920
"'I'm dying, miss.'

4992
06:42:59,040 --> 06:43:02,880
The wound on his hand, the teeth marks, had begun to throb once more,

4993
06:43:02,880 --> 06:43:07,520
and were again becoming visible. This alone would have been enough to fill him with dread.

4994
06:43:08,480 --> 06:43:11,200
"'Have the driver take you to the hospital,' the girl said.

4995
06:43:12,240 --> 06:43:15,120
"'Can we have dinner together?' Joe asked her.

4996
06:43:16,240 --> 06:43:18,640
"'Is that what you want to do?' she said.

4997
06:43:18,640 --> 06:43:19,680
"'When you're—'

4998
06:43:19,680 --> 06:43:23,840
"'Whatever it is, sick? Are you sick?' she opened the door of the cab.

4999
06:43:23,840 --> 06:43:24,000
Then.

5000
06:43:24,880 --> 06:43:27,440
"'Do you want me to go with you to the hospital? Is that it?'

5001
06:43:28,480 --> 06:43:30,240
"'To the matador,' Joe said.

5002
06:43:30,800 --> 06:43:33,360
"'We'll have braised fillet of mushroom-mull cricket.'

5003
06:43:34,240 --> 06:43:38,800
He remembered, then, that imported delicacy did not exist in this time period.

5004
06:43:39,680 --> 06:43:41,040
"'Market steak,' he said.

5005
06:43:41,680 --> 06:43:43,440
"'Beef. Do you like beef?'

5006
06:43:44,400 --> 06:43:46,720
Getting into the cab, the girl said to the driver,

5007
06:43:46,720 --> 06:43:48,160
"'He wants to go to the matador.'

5008
06:43:48,880 --> 06:43:50,560
"'Okay, miss,' the driver said.

5009
06:43:51,120 --> 06:43:53,760
The cab rolled out into traffic once more.

5010
06:43:53,760 --> 06:43:56,480
At the next intersection, the driver made a U-turn.

5011
06:43:56,480 --> 06:43:59,680
"'Now,' Joe realized, we are on our way to the restaurant.

5012
06:43:59,680 --> 06:44:01,120
"'I wonder if I'll make it there.'

5013
06:44:01,840 --> 06:44:05,280
Fatigue and cold had invaded him completely.

5014
06:44:05,280 --> 06:44:09,280
He felt his body processes beginning to close down one by one.

5015
06:44:09,280 --> 06:44:11,120
Organs that had no future.

5016
06:44:11,120 --> 06:44:13,840
The liver did not need to make red blood cells.

5017
06:44:13,840 --> 06:44:16,640
The kidneys did not need to excrete wastes.

5018
06:44:16,640 --> 06:44:19,200
The intestines no longer served any purpose.

5019
06:44:19,840 --> 06:44:21,840
Only the heart laboring on.

5020
06:44:22,480 --> 06:44:25,120
And the increasingly difficult breathing.

5021
06:44:25,120 --> 06:44:29,280
Each time he drew air into his lungs, he sensed the concrete block

5022
06:44:29,280 --> 06:44:31,360
that had situated itself on his chest.

5023
06:44:32,080 --> 06:44:34,320
"'My gravestone,' he decided.

5024
06:44:35,120 --> 06:44:37,360
His hand, he saw, was bleeding again.

5025
06:44:37,360 --> 06:44:39,920
Thick, slow blood appeared, drop by drop.

5026
06:44:40,720 --> 06:44:43,360
"'Care for Lucky Strike?' the girl asked him,

5027
06:44:43,360 --> 06:44:44,960
extending her pack toward him.

5028
06:44:45,520 --> 06:44:48,240
"'They're toasted,' as the slogan goes.

5029
06:44:48,240 --> 06:44:51,440
The phrase LSMFT won't come into existence until—'

5030
06:44:52,240 --> 06:44:52,800
Joe said,

5031
06:44:53,680 --> 06:44:54,960
"'My name is Joe Chipp.

5032
06:44:55,680 --> 06:44:56,960
Do you want me to tell you my name?'

5033
06:44:58,000 --> 06:45:00,320
"'Yes,' he grated and shut his eyes.

5034
06:45:00,320 --> 06:45:02,720
He couldn't speak any further for a time anyhow.

5035
06:45:02,720 --> 06:45:06,000
"'Do you like Des Moines?' he asked her,

5036
06:45:06,000 --> 06:45:07,920
presently concealing his hand from her.

5037
06:45:08,800 --> 06:45:11,360
"'Have you lived here a long time?'

5038
06:45:12,240 --> 06:45:15,280
"'You sound very tired, Mr. Chipp.' the girl said.

5039
06:45:16,080 --> 06:45:18,800
"'Oh, hell,' he said, gesturing.

5040
06:45:19,360 --> 06:45:20,160
"'It doesn't matter.'

5041
06:45:21,360 --> 06:45:22,080
"'Yes, it does.'

5042
06:45:23,120 --> 06:45:25,760
The girl opened her purse, rummaged briskly, within it.

5043
06:45:26,800 --> 06:45:28,880
"'I'm not a deformation of juries.

5044
06:45:28,880 --> 06:45:31,760
I'm not like him,' she indicated the driver.

5045
06:45:32,400 --> 06:45:36,400
"'Or like these little old stores and houses and this dingy street—

5046
06:45:36,400 --> 06:45:38,880
all these people and their neolithic cars.

5047
06:45:38,880 --> 06:45:40,080
"'Here, Mr. Chipp.'

5048
06:45:40,880 --> 06:45:44,000
From her purse she brought an envelope which she passed to him.

5049
06:45:44,000 --> 06:45:45,120
"'This is for you.

5050
06:45:45,120 --> 06:45:46,080
Open it right away.

5051
06:45:46,080 --> 06:45:48,560
I don't think either of us should have delayed so long.'

5052
06:45:49,760 --> 06:45:53,120
With leaden fingers he tore open the envelope.

5053
06:45:53,760 --> 06:45:56,720
In it he found a certificate stately and ornamented.

5054
06:45:57,280 --> 06:45:59,680
The printing on it, however, swam.

5055
06:45:59,680 --> 06:46:01,200
He was too weary now to read.

5056
06:46:02,240 --> 06:46:06,240
"'What say?' he asked her, laying it down on his lap.

5057
06:46:07,280 --> 06:46:10,720
"'From the company that manufactures you, Bick,' the girl said.

5058
06:46:10,720 --> 06:46:14,080
"'It's a guarantee, Mr. Chipp, of a free lifetime supply.

5059
06:46:14,720 --> 06:46:19,520
Free because I know your problem regarding money—your, shall we say, idiosyncrasy—

5060
06:46:20,160 --> 06:46:22,960
and a list on the reverse of all the drugstores which carry it.

5061
06:46:23,600 --> 06:46:27,200
Two drugstores and not abandoned ones in Des Moines.'

5062
06:46:27,200 --> 06:46:28,000
The list did.

5063
06:46:28,000 --> 06:46:30,880
I suggest we go to one first before we eat dinner.

5064
06:46:30,880 --> 06:46:32,400
Here, driver—'

5065
06:46:32,400 --> 06:46:36,160
She leaned forward and handed the driver a slip of paper already written out.

5066
06:46:36,160 --> 06:46:38,240
Take us to this address, and hurry.

5067
06:46:38,240 --> 06:46:39,360
They'll be closing soon.'

5068
06:46:40,480 --> 06:46:43,600
Joe lay back against the seed panting for breath.

5069
06:46:44,560 --> 06:46:48,400
"'We'll make it to the drugstore,' the girl said, and patted his arm reassuringly.

5070
06:46:49,600 --> 06:46:52,400
"'Who are you?' Joe asked her.

5071
06:46:53,120 --> 06:46:56,640
"'My name is Ella—Ella Hyde Runceter, your employer's wife.'

5072
06:46:57,600 --> 06:47:01,680
"'You're here with us,' Joe said.

5073
06:47:01,680 --> 06:47:04,400
"'On this side you're in cold pack.'

5074
06:47:04,400 --> 06:47:08,720
"'As you well know, I have been for some time,' Ella Runceter said.

5075
06:47:08,720 --> 06:47:13,840
"'Fairly soon I'll be reborn into another womb, I think—at least Glenn says so.

5076
06:47:14,400 --> 06:47:19,760
I keep dreaming about a smoky red light, and that's bad—that's not a morally proper womb

5077
06:47:19,760 --> 06:47:20,720
to be born into.'

5078
06:47:21,840 --> 06:47:23,920
She laughed a rich, warm laugh.

5079
06:47:24,880 --> 06:47:27,120
"'You're the other one,' Joe said.

5080
06:47:28,000 --> 06:47:30,400
"'Joy destroying us—you trying to help us.

5081
06:47:31,520 --> 06:47:35,680
Behind you there's no one, just as there's no one behind Jory.

5082
06:47:35,680 --> 06:47:38,080
I've reached the last entities involved.'

5083
06:47:39,280 --> 06:47:40,800
Ella said costically,

5084
06:47:40,800 --> 06:47:42,720
"'I don't think of myself as an entity.

5085
06:47:43,440 --> 06:47:45,760
I usually think of myself as Ella Runceter.'

5086
06:47:46,640 --> 06:47:48,960
"'But it's true,' Joe said.

5087
06:47:49,760 --> 06:47:50,080
"'Yes.'

5088
06:47:50,800 --> 06:47:52,160
Sombrily she nodded.

5089
06:47:53,120 --> 06:47:55,520
"'Why are you working against Jory?'

5090
06:47:56,240 --> 06:47:57,920
"'Because Jory invaded me.'

5091
06:47:58,560 --> 06:47:59,440
Ella said.

5092
06:47:59,440 --> 06:48:02,000
He menaced me in the same way he's menaced you.

5093
06:48:02,720 --> 06:48:04,080
We both know what he does.

5094
06:48:04,080 --> 06:48:06,560
He told you himself in your hotel room.

5095
06:48:06,560 --> 06:48:08,480
Sometimes he becomes very powerful.

5096
06:48:08,480 --> 06:48:12,240
On occasion he manages to supplant me when I'm active and trying to talk to Glenn.

5097
06:48:12,880 --> 06:48:16,240
But I seem to be able to cope with him better than most half-lifers,

5098
06:48:16,240 --> 06:48:18,000
with or without you, Vic.

5099
06:48:18,000 --> 06:48:21,120
Better, for instance, than your group, even acting as a collective.'

5100
06:48:22,160 --> 06:48:23,440
"'Yes,' Joe said.

5101
06:48:24,080 --> 06:48:25,920
It certainly was true, well-proved.'

5102
06:48:26,640 --> 06:48:28,720
"'But I'm reborn,' Ella said.

5103
06:48:28,720 --> 06:48:31,120
Glenn won't be able to consult with me any more.

5104
06:48:31,840 --> 06:48:35,280
"'I have a very selfish, practical reason for assisting you, Mr. Chip.

5105
06:48:35,280 --> 06:48:36,960
I want you to replace me.

5106
06:48:37,600 --> 06:48:41,520
I want to have someone whom Glenn can ask for advice and assistance,

5107
06:48:41,520 --> 06:48:42,640
whom he can lean on.

5108
06:48:43,360 --> 06:48:44,800
You will be ideal.

5109
06:48:44,800 --> 06:48:47,360
You'll be doing in half-life what you did in full life.

5110
06:48:47,920 --> 06:48:50,880
So in a sense I'm not motivated by noble sentiments.

5111
06:48:50,880 --> 06:48:55,200
I saved you from Jory for a good common sense reason,' she added,

5112
06:48:55,200 --> 06:48:57,520
and God knows I detest Jory.'

5113
06:48:58,800 --> 06:49:01,200
"'After you're reborn,' Joe said.

5114
06:49:01,840 --> 06:49:03,040
I won't succumb.

5115
06:49:03,760 --> 06:49:08,160
You have your lifetime supply of you, Vic, as it says on the certificate I gave you.'

5116
06:49:09,200 --> 06:49:09,680
Joe said,

5117
06:49:10,560 --> 06:49:12,640
"'Maybe I can defeat Jory.'

5118
06:49:13,280 --> 06:49:14,800
"'Destroy him, you mean?'

5119
06:49:15,520 --> 06:49:16,480
Ella pondered.

5120
06:49:17,120 --> 06:49:18,880
He is not invulnerable.

5121
06:49:18,880 --> 06:49:22,160
Maybe in time you can learn ways to nullify him.

5122
06:49:22,160 --> 06:49:24,480
I think that's really the best you can hope to do.

5123
06:49:24,480 --> 06:49:28,000
I doubt if you can truly destroy him, in other words, consume him,

5124
06:49:28,000 --> 06:49:31,360
as he does to half-lifers placed near him at the moratorium.'

5125
06:49:32,240 --> 06:49:33,840
"'Hell,' Joe said.

5126
06:49:33,840 --> 06:49:39,760
I'll tell Glenn Runceter the situation, and have him move Jory out of the moratorium entirely.'

5127
06:49:40,320 --> 06:49:42,240
"'Oh, Glenn has no authority to do that.'

5128
06:49:43,440 --> 06:49:45,680
"'Won't Sean Hyde von Vogel sing?'

5129
06:49:46,640 --> 06:49:47,280
Ella said,

5130
06:49:47,840 --> 06:49:52,560
"'Herbits paid a great deal of money annually by Jory's family to keep him with the others,

5131
06:49:52,560 --> 06:49:55,680
and to think up plausible reasons for doing so.

5132
06:49:56,720 --> 06:50:00,400
And there are Jories in every moratorium.

5133
06:50:00,400 --> 06:50:03,040
This battle goes on wherever you have half-lifers.

5134
06:50:03,600 --> 06:50:07,040
It's a verity, a rule of our kind of existence.'

5135
06:50:07,920 --> 06:50:13,360
She lapsed into silence, then, for the first time he saw in her face an expression of anger,

5136
06:50:13,360 --> 06:50:16,720
a ruffled, taut look that disturbed her tranquillity.

5137
06:50:17,440 --> 06:50:21,360
"'It has to be fought on our side of the glass,' Ella said,

5138
06:50:21,360 --> 06:50:24,640
by those of us in half-life, those that Jory prays on.

5139
06:50:25,200 --> 06:50:27,840
"'You'll have to take charge, Mr. Chip, after I'm reborn.

5140
06:50:27,840 --> 06:50:29,520
Do you think you can do that?

5141
06:50:29,520 --> 06:50:30,320
It'll be hard.

5142
06:50:30,880 --> 06:50:35,280
Jory'll be sapping your strength always, putting a burden on you that you'll feel as,'

5143
06:50:36,080 --> 06:50:36,880
she hesitated,

5144
06:50:37,440 --> 06:50:43,920
the approach of death, which it will be, because in half-life we diminish constantly anyhow.

5145
06:50:44,480 --> 06:50:46,000
Jory only speeds it up.

5146
06:50:46,560 --> 06:50:50,640
The weariness and cooling off come anyhow, but not so soon.'

5147
06:50:51,920 --> 06:50:53,200
To himself, Joe thought,

5148
06:50:53,760 --> 06:50:55,840
"'I can remember what he did to Wendy.

5149
06:50:55,840 --> 06:50:57,680
That'll keep me going, that alone.'

5150
06:50:58,960 --> 06:51:01,680
"'Here's their drugstore, Miss,' the driver said.

5151
06:51:01,680 --> 06:51:04,720
The square upright old dodge wheezed the curb and parked.

5152
06:51:05,440 --> 06:51:10,960
"'I won't go in with you,' Ella Ronson said to Joe as he opened the door and crept shakily out.

5153
06:51:10,960 --> 06:51:13,840
"'Good-bye. Thanks for your loyalty to Glenn.

5154
06:51:13,840 --> 06:51:16,240
Thanks for what you're going to be doing for him.'

5155
06:51:17,040 --> 06:51:19,520
She leaned toward him, kissed him on the cheek.

5156
06:51:19,520 --> 06:51:22,160
Her lips seemed to him ripe with life.

5157
06:51:22,960 --> 06:51:24,720
And some of it was conveyed to him.

5158
06:51:24,720 --> 06:51:26,160
He felt slightly stronger.

5159
06:51:26,800 --> 06:51:27,760
"'Good luck with Jory!'

5160
06:51:28,400 --> 06:51:32,000
She settled back, composed herself sedately, her purse on her lap.

5161
06:51:32,960 --> 06:51:37,680
Joe shut the cab door, stood, then made his way haltingly into the drugstore.

5162
06:51:37,680 --> 06:51:39,840
Behind him the cab thub-thub-dough.

5163
06:51:40,400 --> 06:51:42,080
He heard but did not see it go.

5164
06:51:43,360 --> 06:51:46,480
Within the solemn, lamplet interior of the drugstore,

5165
06:51:46,480 --> 06:51:48,960
a bald pharmacist wearing a formal dark vest,

5166
06:51:48,960 --> 06:51:52,400
bow tie, and sharply pressed shark-skin trousers approached him.

5167
06:51:53,200 --> 06:51:56,560
"'Afraid we're closing, sir. I was just coming to lock the door.'

5168
06:51:56,560 --> 06:51:59,280
"'But I'm in,' Joe said, and I want to be weighted on.

5169
06:51:59,920 --> 06:52:03,200
He showed the pharmacist the certificate which Ella had given him,

5170
06:52:03,200 --> 06:52:08,320
squinting through his round rimless glasses the pharmacist labored over the gothic printing.

5171
06:52:09,200 --> 06:52:11,040
"'Are you going to wait on me?' Joe asked.

5172
06:52:12,000 --> 06:52:13,760
"'You beck,' the pharmacist said.

5173
06:52:14,400 --> 06:52:18,240
"'I believe I'm out of that. Let me check and see.' He started off.'

5174
06:52:19,600 --> 06:52:21,040
"'Jory?' Joe said.

5175
06:52:21,840 --> 06:52:23,280
Turning his head, the pharmacist said.

5176
06:52:23,840 --> 06:52:24,080
"'Sir?'

5177
06:52:25,040 --> 06:52:26,880
"'Your jury,' Joe said.

5178
06:52:26,880 --> 06:52:28,800
"'I can tell now,' he said to himself.

5179
06:52:28,800 --> 06:52:30,640
"'I'm learning how to know him when I encounter him.'

5180
06:52:31,360 --> 06:52:36,000
"'You invented this drugstore,' he said, and everything in it except for the spray cans of

5181
06:52:36,000 --> 06:52:40,000
Ubeck. You have no authority over Ubeck. That comes from Ella.'

5182
06:52:40,640 --> 06:52:42,080
He forced himself into motion.

5183
06:52:42,080 --> 06:52:45,840
Step by step he edged his way behind the counter to the shelves of medical supplies,

5184
06:52:46,400 --> 06:52:48,560
peering in the gloom over one shelf after the other.

5185
06:52:48,560 --> 06:52:50,160
He tried to locate the Ubeck.

5186
06:52:50,160 --> 06:52:52,080
The lighting of the store had dimmed.

5187
06:52:52,080 --> 06:52:54,000
The antique fixtures were fading.

5188
06:52:54,960 --> 06:52:58,800
"'I've regressed all the Ubeck in this store,' the pharmacist said in a youthful

5189
06:52:58,800 --> 06:53:00,480
high-pitched jury voice.

5190
06:53:00,480 --> 06:53:02,800
"'Back to the liver and kidney bomb. It's no good now.'

5191
06:53:03,760 --> 06:53:06,640
"'I'll go to the other drugstore that has it,' Joe said.

5192
06:53:07,200 --> 06:53:11,440
He leaned against the counter painfully drawing in slow irregular gulps of air.

5193
06:53:12,240 --> 06:53:15,200
"'Jory from within the balding pharmacist said,

5194
06:53:15,200 --> 06:53:16,080
"'It'll be closed.'

5195
06:53:17,120 --> 06:53:18,960
"'Tomorrow,' Joe said.

5196
06:53:18,960 --> 06:53:21,520
"'I can hold out until tomorrow morning.'

5197
06:53:21,520 --> 06:53:23,440
"'You can,' Jory said.

5198
06:53:23,440 --> 06:53:26,080
"'And anyhow the Ubeck at that drugstore will be regressed too.'

5199
06:53:26,960 --> 06:53:29,120
"'Another town,' Joe said.

5200
06:53:29,120 --> 06:53:31,120
"'Wherever you go it'll be regressed.

5201
06:53:31,120 --> 06:53:34,800
Back to the salve, or back to the powder, or back to the elixir,

5202
06:53:34,800 --> 06:53:37,920
or back to the bomb. You'll never see a spray can of it, Joe Chipp.'

5203
06:53:38,720 --> 06:53:43,200
Jory, in the form of the bald-headed pharmacist's smile showing celluloid-like

5204
06:53:43,200 --> 06:53:49,840
dentures. "'I can,' he broke off, gathering his meager vitality to him,

5205
06:53:49,840 --> 06:53:53,920
trying by his own strength to warm his stiffening cold-numbed body.

5206
06:53:55,040 --> 06:53:59,120
"'Bring it up to the present,' he said, to 1992.'

5207
06:54:00,320 --> 06:54:05,360
"'Can you, Mr. Chipp?' the pharmacist handed Joe a square paste-board container.

5208
06:54:05,360 --> 06:54:07,360
"'Here you are. Open it, and you'll see.'

5209
06:54:08,320 --> 06:54:09,120
Joe said.

5210
06:54:09,120 --> 06:54:10,080
"'I know what I'll see.'

5211
06:54:11,040 --> 06:54:14,720
He concentrated on the blue jar of liver and kidney-bomb.

5212
06:54:14,720 --> 06:54:18,720
"'Evolve forward,' he said to it, flooding it with his need.

5213
06:54:18,720 --> 06:54:22,000
He poured whatever energy he had left into the container.

5214
06:54:22,800 --> 06:54:23,840
"'It did not change.'

5215
06:54:24,560 --> 06:54:27,040
"'This is the regular world,' he said to it.

5216
06:54:27,040 --> 06:54:30,560
"'Spray can,' he said aloud, he shut his eyes, resting.

5217
06:54:30,560 --> 06:54:33,120
"'It's not a spray can, Mr. Chipp,' the pharmacist said.

5218
06:54:33,760 --> 06:54:36,640
Going here and there in the drugstore he shut off lights.

5219
06:54:36,640 --> 06:54:39,840
At the cash register he punched a key and the drawer rattled open.

5220
06:54:39,840 --> 06:54:43,280
Expertly the pharmacist transferred the bills and changed from the drawer

5221
06:54:43,280 --> 06:54:45,040
into a metal box with a lock on it.

5222
06:54:46,160 --> 06:54:50,480
"'You are a spray can,' Joe said to the paste-board container,

5223
06:54:50,480 --> 06:54:51,520
which he held in his hand.

5224
06:54:52,160 --> 06:54:58,800
"'This is 1992,' he said, and tried to exert everything he put the entirety of himself

5225
06:54:58,800 --> 06:55:03,440
into the effort. The last light blinked out, turned off by the pseudo-pharmacist.

5226
06:55:04,000 --> 06:55:08,080
A dull gleam shone into the drugstore from the street lamp outside.

5227
06:55:08,080 --> 06:55:12,800
By it Joe could make out the shape of the object in his hand, its box-like lines.

5228
06:55:13,360 --> 06:55:15,120
Opening the door the pharmacist said,

5229
06:55:15,120 --> 06:55:17,040
"'Come on, Mr. Chipp, time to go home.'

5230
06:55:17,040 --> 06:55:18,240
She was wrong, wasn't she?

5231
06:55:18,240 --> 06:55:21,520
And you won't see her again because she's so far on the road to being reborn.

5232
06:55:21,520 --> 06:55:24,640
She's not thinking about you anymore, or me, or Runceter.

5233
06:55:24,640 --> 06:55:28,960
Would L.A.C.'s now or various lights, red and dingy, then maybe bright orange?'

5234
06:55:29,680 --> 06:55:34,240
"'What I hold here,' Joe said, "'is a spray can.'"

5235
06:55:34,960 --> 06:55:36,640
"'Nope,' the pharmacist said.

5236
06:55:36,640 --> 06:55:38,880
"'I'm sorry, Mr. Chipp, I really am, but it's not.'"

5237
06:55:40,800 --> 06:55:44,240
Joe set the paste-board container down on a nearby counter.

5238
06:55:44,240 --> 06:55:50,560
He turned with dignity, and began the long, slow journey across the drugstore to the front door,

5239
06:55:50,560 --> 06:55:55,600
which the pharmacist held open for him. Neither of them spoke until Joe at last

5240
06:55:55,600 --> 06:55:59,120
passed through the doorway and out onto the nocturnal sidewalk.

5241
06:55:59,920 --> 06:56:04,400
Behind him the pharmacist emerged to. He bent and locked the door after the two of them.

5242
06:56:05,200 --> 06:56:08,800
"'I think I'll complain to the manufacturer,' Joe said.

5243
06:56:08,800 --> 06:56:09,520
"'About the—'

5244
06:56:10,240 --> 06:56:13,600
He ceased, talking something constricted his throat.

5245
06:56:13,600 --> 06:56:15,680
He could not breathe, and he could not speak.

5246
06:56:16,480 --> 06:56:18,320
Then temporarily the blockage abated.

5247
06:56:19,280 --> 06:56:21,840
"'Your regressed drugstore,' he finished.

5248
06:56:22,480 --> 06:56:24,240
"'Good night,' the pharmacist said.

5249
06:56:24,800 --> 06:56:27,840
He remained for a moment, eyeing Joe in the evening gloom,

5250
06:56:27,840 --> 06:56:29,520
then shrugging, he started off.

5251
06:56:30,880 --> 06:56:35,280
To his left Joe made out the dark shape of a bench where people waited for a streetcar.

5252
06:56:35,280 --> 06:56:37,600
He managed to reach it to seat himself.

5253
06:56:38,240 --> 06:56:42,640
The other persons, two or three, whichever it was, squeezed away from him,

5254
06:56:42,640 --> 06:56:46,960
either out of aversion or to give him room he could not tell which, and he didn't care.

5255
06:56:47,520 --> 06:56:50,560
All he felt was the support of the bench beneath him,

5256
06:56:50,560 --> 06:56:53,520
the release of some of his vast inertial weight.

5257
06:56:54,400 --> 06:56:56,960
"'A few more minutes,' he said to himself.

5258
06:56:56,960 --> 06:56:58,240
"'If I remember right—'

5259
06:56:59,280 --> 06:57:04,240
Christ, what a thing to have to go through,' he said to himself for the second time.

5260
06:57:05,280 --> 06:57:10,720
Anyhow, we tried,' he thought as he watched the yellow flickering lights and neon signs,

5261
06:57:10,720 --> 06:57:14,240
the flow of cars going in both directions directly before his eyes.

5262
06:57:15,200 --> 06:57:18,320
He thought to himself, runse to the kit and struggled.

5263
06:57:18,320 --> 06:57:22,400
Ella has been scratching and biting and gouging for a long time,

5264
06:57:22,400 --> 06:57:27,200
and he thought, I damn near evolved the jar of ubeck liver and kidney bomb back to the present.

5265
06:57:27,200 --> 06:57:31,600
I almost succeeded. There was something in knowing that,

5266
06:57:31,600 --> 06:57:36,480
an awareness of his own great strength, his final transcendental attempt.'

5267
06:57:37,760 --> 06:57:43,040
The streetcar, a clanging metal enormity, came to a grating halt before the bench.

5268
06:57:43,040 --> 06:57:47,200
The several people beside Joe rose and hurried out to board it by its rear platform.

5269
06:57:47,840 --> 06:57:50,240
"'Aye, mister,' the conductor yelled to Joe.

5270
06:57:50,240 --> 06:57:53,600
"'Are you coming or aren't you?' Joe said nothing.

5271
06:57:54,160 --> 06:57:57,280
The conductor waited. Then jerked his signal cord.

5272
06:57:57,280 --> 06:58:00,960
Noisily the streetcar started up. It continued on,

5273
06:58:00,960 --> 06:58:03,840
and then at last disappeared beyond his range of vision.

5274
06:58:04,720 --> 06:58:09,680
"'Lots of luck,' Joe said to himself, as he heard the racket of the streetcar's wheels die away.

5275
06:58:10,320 --> 06:58:14,800
And so long.' He leaned back, closed his eyes.

5276
06:58:15,680 --> 06:58:17,520
"'Excuse me?'

5277
06:58:18,800 --> 06:58:23,040
Bending over him in the darkness a girl in a synthetic ostrich leather coat,

5278
06:58:23,680 --> 06:58:25,760
he looked up at her jarred into awareness.

5279
06:58:26,640 --> 06:58:28,160
"'Mr. Chip,' she said.

5280
06:58:29,040 --> 06:58:32,240
Pretty and slender, dressed in hat, gloves, suit, and high heels.

5281
06:58:32,800 --> 06:58:35,600
She held something in her hand. He saw the outlines of a package.

5282
06:58:36,160 --> 06:58:40,560
Of New York? Of Runciter Associates? I don't want to give this to the wrong person.'

5283
06:58:40,640 --> 06:58:43,840
"'I'm Joe Chip,' he said.

5284
06:58:44,800 --> 06:58:48,960
For a moment he thought the girl might be Ella Runciter, but he had never seen her before.

5285
06:58:49,840 --> 06:58:51,920
"'Who sent you?' he said.

5286
06:58:52,800 --> 06:58:55,040
"'Dr. Sunderbar,' the girl said.

5287
06:58:55,040 --> 06:58:58,640
The younger Dr. Sunderbar, son of Dr. Sunderbar the founder.

5288
06:58:59,840 --> 06:59:00,720
"'Who's that?'

5289
06:59:01,600 --> 06:59:05,040
The name meant nothing to him, and then he remembered where he had seen it.

5290
06:59:05,600 --> 06:59:08,160
The liver and kidney man,' he said.

5291
06:59:08,880 --> 06:59:14,560
"'Processed oleander leaves, oil of peppermint, charcoal, cobalt, chloride, zinc oxide.'

5292
06:59:15,280 --> 06:59:17,440
Wearing this overcame him, he stopped talking.

5293
06:59:18,480 --> 06:59:19,200
The girl said,

5294
06:59:19,920 --> 06:59:23,680
"'By making use of the most advanced techniques of modern-day science,

5295
06:59:23,680 --> 06:59:29,600
the reversion of matter to earlier forms can be reversed, and at a price any conept owner can

5296
06:59:29,600 --> 06:59:34,080
afford. UBIC is sold by leading home-art stores throughout earth,

5297
06:59:34,080 --> 06:59:36,400
so look for it at the place you shop, Mr. Chip.'"

5298
06:59:37,680 --> 06:59:39,120
Fully conscious now he said,

5299
06:59:40,000 --> 06:59:44,400
"'Look for it where?' he struggled to his feet, stood inexperently swaying.

5300
06:59:44,960 --> 06:59:49,040
"'You're from 1992, what you said came from Runciter's TV commercial.'

5301
06:59:49,920 --> 06:59:54,240
An evening wind rustled at him, and he felt a tug at him, drawing him away with it.

5302
06:59:54,240 --> 06:59:59,440
He seemed to be like some ragged bundle of webs and cloth barely holding together.

5303
07:00:00,240 --> 07:00:02,960
"'Yes, Mr. Chip,' the girl handed him a package.

5304
07:00:03,600 --> 07:00:08,240
"'You brought me from the future. By what you did there inside the drug-store a few moments ago,

5305
07:00:08,240 --> 07:00:10,240
you summoned me directly from the factory.

5306
07:00:11,040 --> 07:00:14,720
Mr. Chip, I could spray it on you if you're too weak to, shall I?

5307
07:00:14,720 --> 07:00:19,440
I'm an official factory representative and technical consultant. I know how to apply it.'

5308
07:00:20,160 --> 07:00:23,760
She took the package swiftly back from his trembling hands, tearing it open.

5309
07:00:23,760 --> 07:00:25,680
She immediately sprayed him with UBIC.

5310
07:00:26,320 --> 07:00:30,720
In the dusk he saw the spray can glint, he saw the happy, colored lettering.

5311
07:00:32,160 --> 07:00:37,360
"'Thanks,' he said after a time, after he felt better and warmer.

5312
07:00:38,480 --> 07:00:42,640
The girl said, "'You didn't need as much this time as you did in the hotel room.

5313
07:00:42,640 --> 07:00:47,520
You must be stronger than before. Here, take the can of it. You might need it before morning.'

5314
07:00:48,800 --> 07:00:51,680
"'Can I get more?' Joe said, when this runs out.'

5315
07:00:52,640 --> 07:00:57,760
"'Evidently so. If you got me here once, I would assume you can get me here again the same way.'

5316
07:00:58,560 --> 07:01:04,160
She moved away from him, merging with the shadows created by the dense walls of closed-up nearby

5317
07:01:04,160 --> 07:01:09,120
stores. "'What is UBIC?' Joe said, wanting her to stay.'

5318
07:01:09,680 --> 07:01:12,160
"'A spray can of UBIC,' the girl answered,

5319
07:01:12,160 --> 07:01:16,480
is a portable negative ionizer with a self-contained high-voltage low-amp unit

5320
07:01:16,480 --> 07:01:22,880
powered by a peak-gain helium battery of 25 kV. The negative ions are given a counterclockwise

5321
07:01:22,880 --> 07:01:29,440
spin by a radically biased acceleration chamber, which creates a centripetal tendency to them

5322
07:01:29,440 --> 07:01:34,720
so that they cohere rather than dissipate. A negative ion field diminishes the velocity

5323
07:01:34,720 --> 07:01:40,000
of antiproto-phasons normally present in the atmosphere. As soon as their velocity falls,

5324
07:01:40,000 --> 07:01:45,440
they cease to be antiproto-phasons, and under the principle of parity no longer can unite

5325
07:01:45,440 --> 07:01:51,200
with the proto-phasons radiated from persons frozen in coal-pack, that is, those in half-life.

5326
07:01:51,200 --> 07:01:57,840
The end result is that the proportion of proto-phasons not cancelled by antiproto-phasons increases,

5327
07:01:57,840 --> 07:02:04,160
which means, for a specific time anyhow, an increment in the net put forth field of proto-phasonic

5328
07:02:04,160 --> 07:02:10,480
activity, which the affected half-liver experiences as greater vitality, plus a lowering of the

5329
07:02:10,480 --> 07:02:16,240
experience of low coal-pack temperatures, so you can see why regressed forms of ubiquic fail to—

5330
07:02:17,040 --> 07:02:22,320
Joe said reflexively, to say negative ions is redundant, all ions are negative.

5331
07:02:23,680 --> 07:02:25,120
Again the girl moved away.

5332
07:02:26,000 --> 07:02:31,760
Maybe I'll see you again, she said gently. It was rewarding to bring you the spray can.

5333
07:02:31,760 --> 07:02:32,560
Maybe next time—

5334
07:02:33,280 --> 07:02:38,000
Maybe we can have dinner together, Joe said. I look forward to it.

5335
07:02:38,000 --> 07:02:40,000
She ebbed farther and farther away.

5336
07:02:40,800 --> 07:02:46,960
Who invented, Eubrick, Joe asked? A number of responsible half-lifers whom Jory threatened,

5337
07:02:46,960 --> 07:02:53,040
but principally by Ella Runceter. It took her and them working together a long, long time,

5338
07:02:53,040 --> 07:02:55,440
and there still isn't very much of it available as yet.

5339
07:02:56,240 --> 07:03:03,440
Ebbing from him in her trim covert way she continued to retreat, and then, by degrees, was gone.

5340
07:03:04,400 --> 07:03:10,480
At the matador, Joe called after her. I understand Jory did a good job materializing it,

5341
07:03:11,280 --> 07:03:17,760
or regressing it just right, whatever it is he does. He listened, but the girl did not answer.

5342
07:03:19,280 --> 07:03:24,080
Carefully carrying the spray can of Eubrick, Joe Chipp walked out to greet the evening traffic,

5343
07:03:24,080 --> 07:03:28,640
searching for a cab. Under a street light he held up the spray can of Eubrick,

5344
07:03:28,640 --> 07:03:29,920
read the printing on the label.

5345
07:03:29,920 --> 07:03:37,520
I think her name is Myra Laney. Look on reverse side of container for address and phone number.

5346
07:03:38,640 --> 07:03:45,360
Thanks, Joe said to the spray can. We are served by organic ghosts, he thought,

5347
07:03:45,920 --> 07:03:49,840
who, speaking and writing, pass through this our new environment,

5348
07:03:50,400 --> 07:03:56,720
watching wise physical ghosts from the full life world, elements of which have become for us

5349
07:03:56,800 --> 07:04:01,600
invading but agreeable splinters of a substance that pulsates like a former heart.

5350
07:04:02,560 --> 07:04:08,000
And of all of them, he thought, thanks to Glenn Runciter, in particular, the writer of

5351
07:04:08,000 --> 07:04:15,120
instructions, labels, and notes, valuable notes. He raised his arm to slow to a grumpy halt,

5352
07:04:15,120 --> 07:04:21,840
a passing 1936 Graham cab. 17.

5353
07:04:22,720 --> 07:04:31,440
I am Eubick. Before the universe was, I am. I made the suns, I made the worlds,

5354
07:04:31,440 --> 07:04:37,760
I created the lives and the places they inhabit. I move them here, I put them there,

5355
07:04:37,760 --> 07:04:44,240
they go as I say, they do as I tell them. I am the word and my name is never spoken,

5356
07:04:44,240 --> 07:04:51,120
the name which no one knows. I am called Eubick, but that is not my name. I am.

5357
07:04:51,840 --> 07:04:53,440
I shall always be. 17.

5358
07:04:56,160 --> 07:04:58,640
Glenn Runciter could not find the moratorium owner.

5359
07:04:59,200 --> 07:05:04,640
Are you sure you don't know where he is? Runciter asked Miss Beeson, the moratorium owner's secretary.

5360
07:05:04,640 --> 07:05:06,880
It's essential that I talk to Ella again.

5361
07:05:06,880 --> 07:05:10,400
18. I'll have her brought out, Ms. Beeson said.

5362
07:05:10,960 --> 07:05:16,640
You may use Office 4B. Please wait there, Mr. Runciter. I will have your wife for you in a

5363
07:05:16,640 --> 07:05:18,960
very short time. Try to make yourself comfortable.

5364
07:05:18,960 --> 07:05:25,840
19. Locating Office 4B, Runciter paced about restlessly. At last a moratorium attendant appeared,

5365
07:05:25,840 --> 07:05:28,080
wheeling in Ella's casket on a hand truck.

5366
07:05:28,080 --> 07:05:31,280
20. Sorry to keep you waiting, the attendant said.

5367
07:05:31,280 --> 07:05:36,720
He began at once to set up the electronic communing mechanism, humming happily as he worked.

5368
07:05:36,720 --> 07:05:41,040
In short order, the task was completed. The attendant checked the circuit one last time,

5369
07:05:41,040 --> 07:05:44,320
knotted in satisfaction, then started to leave the office.

5370
07:05:44,960 --> 07:05:49,520
This is for you, Runciter said, and handed him several fifty-cent pieces, which he had

5371
07:05:49,520 --> 07:05:55,280
scrounged from his various pockets. I appreciate the rapidity with which you accomplished the job.

5372
07:05:56,080 --> 07:06:01,360
Thank you, Mr. Runciter, the attendant said. He glanced at the coins, then frowned.

5373
07:06:02,160 --> 07:06:08,560
What kind of money is this, he said. Runciter took a good long look at the fifty-cent pieces.

5374
07:06:08,640 --> 07:06:12,400
20. He saw at once what the attendant meant.

5375
07:06:12,400 --> 07:06:15,920
21. Very definitely the coins were not as they should be.

5376
07:06:15,920 --> 07:06:22,560
Whose profile is this, he asked himself. Who's this on all three coins? Not the right person at all.

5377
07:06:23,200 --> 07:06:26,880
And yet he's familiar. I know him.

5378
07:06:26,880 --> 07:06:30,240
21. And then he recognized the profile.

5379
07:06:30,240 --> 07:06:34,160
22. I wonder what this means, he asked himself.

5380
07:06:34,160 --> 07:06:37,040
23. Strangest thing I've ever seen.

5381
07:06:38,000 --> 07:06:44,720
Most things in life eventually can be explained, but... Joe Chip on a fifty-cent piece?

5382
07:06:46,320 --> 07:06:49,120
It was the first Joe Chip money he had ever seen.

5383
07:06:50,400 --> 07:06:55,520
He had an intuition, chillingly, that if he searched his pockets and his billfold,

5384
07:06:55,520 --> 07:07:00,080
he would find more. This was just the beginning.

5385
07:07:00,080 --> 07:07:10,800
21. This concludes the reading of UBIK by Philip K. Dick.

